1 (4) shall require a candidate who accepts public campaign financing to:
2 (i) establish a campaign finance entity solely for the campaign for
3 [county] LOCAL elective office; and
4 (ii) use funds from that campaign finance entity only for the
5 campaign for [county] LOCAL elective office;
6 (5) shall prohibit a candidate who accepts public campaign financing from
7 transferring funds:
8 (i) to the campaign finance entity established to finance the
9 campaign for [county] LOCAL elective office from any other campaign finance entity
10 established for the candidate; and
11 (ii) from the campaign finance entity established to finance the
12 campaign for [county] LOCAL elective office to any other campaign finance entity;
13 (6) shall provide for a public election fund for [county] LOCAL elective
14 offices that is administered by the chief financial officer of the county; and
15 (7) shall be subject to regulation and oversight by the State Board to ensure
16 conformity with State law and policy to the extent practicable.
17 (d) A system of public campaign financing enacted under subsection (b) of this
18 section may:
19 (1) provide for more stringent regulation of campaign finance activity by
20 candidates who choose to accept public campaign financing, including contributions,
21 expenditures, reporting, and campaign material, than is provided for by State law;
22 (2) provide for administrative penalties for violations, in accordance with §
23 10–202 of the Local Government Article; and
24 (3) allow a publicly financed candidate to transfer any amount of funds
25 from the candidate’s campaign finance entity to the candidate’s contested election
26 committee.
27 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
28 1, 2025.

